benign /bɪˈnaɪn/

1. ADJ You use benign to describe someone who is kind, gentle, and harmless. 和善的 

例： They are normally a more benign audience. 他们通常是更为和善的观众。 

2. benignly ADV 和善地 

例： I just smiled benignly and stood back. 我只是和善地笑了笑，就退到了后边。 

3. ADJ A benign substance or process does not have any harmful effects. 无害的 

例： We're taking relatively benign medicines and we're turning them into poisons. 我们拿相对无害的药品，把它们转化成毒药。 

4. ADJ A benign tumour will not cause death or serious harm. 良性的 [医学] 

例： It wasn't cancer, only a benign tumour. 这不是癌，只是良性肿瘤。 

5. ADJ Benign conditions are pleasant or make it easy for something to happen. 宜人的 

例： They enjoyed an especially benign climate. 他们那里的气候十分宜人。

